KwaZulu-Natal families, whose loved ones have died of Covid-19, say they’re having to abandon some cultural practices. And this is adding to the pain of their loss. The province is currently experiencing a spike in coronavirus infections and deaths. eNCA's Thuba Vilane has more. Courtesy #DStv403  PORT SHEPSTONE - KwaZulu-Natal families whose loved ones have died of COVID-19 say they’re having to abandon some cultural practices. This is adding to the pain of their loss. The province is currently experiencing a spike in coronavirus infections and deaths. READ: COVID-19 in SA: 18,000 new cases recorded Funeral homes are also struggling with the huge number of funerals they have to conduct at the moment. Undertakers say they are asking for a little more understanding from bereaved families. * eNCA's Thuba Vilane reports.